vivae.ros.simulator.server.services

Class AgentSpawnServiceResponseBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • vivae.ros.simulator.server.services.AgentSpawnServiceResponseBuilder
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.ros.node.service.ServiceResponseBuilder<vivae.SpawnRequest,vivae.SpawnResponse>

    public class AgentSpawnServiceResponseBuilder
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.ros.node.service.ServiceResponseBuilder<vivae.SpawnRequest,vivae.SpawnResponse>
    This spawns agents in the ViVae simulation. After loading map, the arena contains agent bodies which are not controlled. In order to control agent in the arena, the agent needs to be registered. In order to control the agent over the ROS network, the agent has to communicate over the ROS network (publish/subscribe here). This service tries to register agent in the arena, if success, it opens the ROS communication channels for the agent and returns all necessary information.
